Third-party components
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. null-luo/btrace
   Source:   https://github.com/null-luo/btrace
   Writeup:  https://bbs.kanxue.com/thread-281895.htm

   The BPF capture loop in daemon/binder_transaction.byte.c and the original
   ringbuf chunking design originate from this project. The BPF source file
   itself declares "Dual MIT/GPL" via its SEC("license") string, as required
   for loading into the Linux kernel. The upstream repository does not ship
   a top-level LICENSE file and appears to be unmaintained; redistribution
   here relies on the in-file MIT portion of that dual declaration. If the
   original author wishes to clarify or revoke this, please open an issue.

2. libbpf headers (libbpf v0.6.1)
   Source:   https://github.com/libbpf/libbpf
   License:  BSD-2-Clause
   Location: daemon/headers/ (see daemon/headers/LICENSE.BSD-2-Clause)

   Vendored unmodified; refresh with daemon/headers/update.sh.
